<br>
and i never make fun or take advantage of newbies, unless they're new alts of my friends <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . i've had some very nice talks with low and mid-level rangers who just wanted to ask me a question. and it's happened the other way around too - some of my friends that i have now i first met while i was playing a new character and they were friendly or tried to give me something or whatever.<br>
<br>
basically i think you've just been unlucky, there's plenty of nice people on our server. where you hunt changes things too... some newbie zones like nektulos are horrible because half the things there are kos to DE's and the guardians run around stealing your kills... crushbone and blackburrow get alot of trains but i don't remember finding as many blatantly stupid people there like i have in EC (which is one place i'll never understand why anybody hunts there. steamfont is ok, but there's that big thing which runs around and kills you alot, and the guards aren't in the immediate area. gfay is ok if you get off the beaten track (like away from the old druid ring). qeynos is nice until about level 5, after that there's qeynos hills which isn't too bad either. everfrost is easy to get lost in and there's those skeletons like the vengeful soloist running around. fob is good too and can support a large level range but the guards are far away. i haven't had the chance to try the erudite zones, innothule, or feerott yet. basically, it all depends on what faults you can live with and what faults you can't... if you really wanted to, you could get some friends together at level 5 and go to EW to hunt snow bunnies <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><B><I>Glaurung, the Worm of Morgoth</I></B><BR>
